io.grpc

Interface TransportManager.InterimTransport<T>

  • Enclosing class:
    TransportManager<T>

    public static interface TransportManager.InterimTransport<T>
    A transport provided as a temporary holder of new requests, which will be eventually transferred to real transports or fail.
    See Also:
    TransportManager.createInterimTransport()

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void closeWithError(Status error)
      Closes the interim transport by failing all pending RPCs with the given error.

      Closes the interim transport by transferring pending RPCs to the given real transports.

      • transport

        T transport()
        Returns the transport object.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if closeWithRealTransports(com.google.common.base.Supplier<T>) or closeWithError(io.grpc.Status) has been called

      • closeWithRealTransports

        void closeWithRealTransports(Supplier<T> realTransports)
        Closes the interim transport by transferring pending RPCs to the given real transports.

        Each pending RPC will result in an invocation to Supplier.get() once.

        void closeWithError(Status error)
        Closes the interim transport by failing all pending RPCs with the given error.
